James Clark is heavily involved in text markup, xml and sgml.  His home page is http://jclark.com/ although it appears that he's mostly working from http://thaiopensource.com these days.

Software he's written:

* GNU Groff
* nsgmls
* expat
* nxml-mode

He's also been heavily involved in writing many specifications, in particular XSLT and RelaxNG.

